ordinarily, costs follow the event and a successful litigant receives costs in the absence of special circumstances justifying some other order: ruddock v vardarlis (no 2) (2002) 115 fcr 229 at 235.
so, if an issue by issue approach will produce a result that is fairer than the traditional rule, it should be applied.
in western australia, the supreme court rules provide that costs should follow the event of each pleaded cause of action: see r 66(2)(a).